REASONING: CPF Board (official) states: Withdrawals from age 55 onwards and Important: The minimum withdrawal age for CPF savings is 55 years old, not 50.
Singapore Ministry of Manpower (official) states: The CPF withdrawal age is 55 years old and Any information suggesting withdrawal at age 50 is incorrect and may be fraudulent.

Ask.gov.sg (official government Q&A) confirms: The minimum age for CPF withdrawal is 55 years old. You cannot withdraw your CPF at 50. Special withdrawals only for specific cases (medical grounds or leaving Singapore permanently).
